title.text: Opioid Overdose Death Rate by State
subtitle: The map shows the opioid overdose death rate by state per selected year.
The color scale represents the death rate and darker colors indicate higher death rates.
Some states do not have data for certain years and they are shown in light gray.
Click on a state tile to see the unemployment rates for that state in a selected year.
When on state map view, click anywhere outside the map to return to the full map view
Hover over a state to see the name of the state, death rate, and year.

The bar chart shows the trend of unemployment rate by month in a selected state and year.
If there is no data for a particular state and year, it will be labeled as "No Data".
When a state is selected, the unemployement rate per month is displayed at the top of each bar.
Drag the slider to see yearly unemployment trend of a particular state.
It appears that Michigan had the highest unemployment rate (14.3%) in June and July 2009.
